            p(id='intro').
               Welcome! Come on in, make yourself comfortable, kick back and enjoy your favorite beverage and snack while you take a look around!
              Here you will learn more about myself and more about the world wide web and its many wonders of Html and CSS that creates the  websites and
              webpages for you to browse!

            section(class="html") 
              h2(id="html")  HTML   
              article 
                
                h3(class="author")  A Few Interesting Things I Learned About Html
                h4(class="author")  Charlyn Woodruff 
                h4(class="author")  Sept.22, 2022
                div(class="article_content") 

                  p.
                    Html and CSS are very interesting topics to learn about! What so many people don't realize is that every page you visit on the web has 
                    Html code embedded in those pages. Each page consists of Html code which displays the text, images, and content of each page. Believe it 
                    or not every page you visit from your email to the websites you shop on has embedded code in those pages. One of the most interesting 
                    facts that I learned about Html and the coolest is that most people don't even know that its there!
                            
                  p.
                    All websites are just separate Html pages that are linked together with hyperlinks. Hyperlinks are the just the links you click on to view  
                    a new webpage or new content on another webpage. All of these webpages are linked together by the same navigation links on every page of 
                    website! These links are what help you to navigate any website, blog, social media, or shopping sites. Without Html there are no webpages 
                    and without hyperlinks there is no navigation for websites.

            section(class="css") 
              h2(id="css")  CSS   
              article 
                
                h3(class="author")  Without CSS Our Webpages Would Be Boring
                h4(class="author")  Charlyn Woodruff
                h4(class="author")  Sept. 22,2022
                div(class="article_content") 

                  p.
                    While Html code frames the structure of a webpage, CSS is like crayons are to a coloring book. Without CSS is there is no color or design to
                    the webpages. CSS is one of my favorite subjects to learn more about! CSS allows you to change the color of your text, titles, background 
                    colors, add background images and so much more. CSS can be so specific that you can make only on element styled a certain way while leaving
                    all the rest untouched. Everything you see on these pages on my website are all created with b) i) Html/i) /b)  and b) i) CSS/i) /b)   code.
                    It's an amazing world behind the visual content you see on websites! Just like with computer programs you use, they run and perform tasks 
                    but behind that is another amazing world of code!
