            p(id="about_me").
              We are only here for a short time, and tomorrow is <b> not</b> promised to <b> anyone</b> , so I try to make the most of each day,
              the best I can. I hope I make happy memories for my family, friends, and classmates  and leave a small piece of myself behind. I try to treat 
              others the way I would like to be treated and try to make other peoples days just a little better. All it takes is a smile, a hug, a funny joke,
              or just a moment of kindness to change someones day for the better. 

            section(class="html") 
              article
                h2 A Little Bit About My Family & Me  
                div(class = "section_content") 
                      
                  p.
                    I never know where to begin, I'm usually a pretty quiet person. I like to be around people who are at ease with who they are, who are honest
                    and trustworthy and upfront. I don't always take life so seriously every moment of the day, I feel laughter is good for the soul and the 
                    mind. 
                  p.
                    I grew up and have lived in WV most of my life. I graduated in 1986 from Brooke High School. (Ikr? thats a long time ago lol!)  
                    At that point in time, there wasn't the world wide web internet and cell phones didn't exist then either! While in high school I took every
                    available computer class I could and at that time we learned DOS and binary and not much more. Even then I wanted to learn more and wanted
                    a career in computers. My family consists of my 3 daughters, my husband and myself, 7 cats, 2 hamsters, 2 fish aquariums with lots of 
                    guppies and and 6 hermit crabs.
      
                  p.
                    I married my husband in 1989, moved to Hilton Head Island, S.C. in 1990, we had our first daughter in 1993, our second daughter in 1995 
                    and our youngest daughter in 2004. My youngest daughter just graduated from high school in May 2022. My oldest daughter graduated from WVNCC
                    in 2015 as Registered Health Information Technician  and was hired as a WVU Medicine Hospital coder and now is enjoying being an at home 
                    coder for them. My middle daughter graduated from the WV Corrections Academy and was a CO3 Correctional Officer at WV Doddridge County 
                    Correctional Facility for 4 years, and  she is now a black hat coalminer in Marshall County and has a 5 year old son (my grandson) . 
                    My children became my life, I put them first and foremost and set aside any thought of a career to raise my family and give them the best 
                    start I could in their life.

                  p.
                      Fast forward many years to 2010 when I wanted to branch my art into areas where I didn't have to find storage for things like my polymer 
                      clay sculptures that I made and sold. This is where I started to teach myself the art of graphic design and learning to build and change
                      my own websites for my art. Now that my youngest daughter had graduated from high school, my husband finished his Highway Engineering 
                      degree and graduated from Bridge Valley, I decided to pursue a degree in working with computers. This was something I've wanted to do for 
                      myself since I graduated from high school so many years ago and now had the opportunity to do it, so with the encouragement of my 
                      husband and my children, I enrolled in the WVNCC CIT Software Engineering degree program.
            section(class="html") 
